Remove AwakeMonitor
Awake monitor is only necessary for UniTask due to how Unity Monobehaviours functioned. Specifically, MonoBehaviours would not call OnDestroy if they were not awaked first. Therefore UniTask had to rely on checking if the MonoBehaviour was set to null to detect if the MonoBehavior was destroyed.
However in Godot, Predelete is always called when a node is freed, so there's no need to handle any edge cases.
See https://github.com/Cysharp/UniTask/issues/435 the use of AwakeMonitor in UniTask.
